Anyone ever see that b-list horror film with a literal "You die in the game you die in real life" plot?
It was pretty cool, in concept
It had the stereotypical cheesy "game footage" segments
You know, the ones where they animate gameplay for the sake of a movie, and you KNOW it's not a real game :P
The idea was the game was based around an old mansion in the area it showed up in
You played the game, trying to solve the mystery of what happened there, and if your avatar died in the game, some time later a spirit would find and kill you in a gruesome manner
And you couldn't just stop playing the game, because eventually it would keep playing without you.
And the most interesting part is that you could have a person in the real world affect the game world and vice-versa
A good example would be when one of the people got trapped in an attic room by 3 spirits, and one of the other people played the game and had their avatar find their friend
They used a rose from their inventory and momentarily repel the ghosts to let their friend escape
Quality wise, it's your typical syfy channel original movie schlock, but the concept was so interesting
I feel like I missed something
The day where VR takes THE step of full immersion, that would the day where new places of interest would be built.
